about.description:
The goal of the SteemData project is to make data from the
STEEM blockchain more accessible to developers, researchers
and 3rd party services.
about.summary: Python Utilities for parsing STEEM blockchain

name: steemdata
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "steemdata" %}
{% set version = "2.3" %}
{% set sha256 = "593a390609da04d0c59428b07502f98044e5c2d5aafbe89f568aac1078cb8a84" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256|lower }}

build:
  number: 1000
  skip: True  # [py<34]
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - pip

  run:
    - python
    - pymongo
    - python-dateutil
    - requests
    - funcy
    - werkzeug

test:
  imports:
    - steemdata

  commands:
    - conda inspect linkages -p $PREFIX steemdata  # [not win]
    - conda inspect objects -p $PREFIX steemdata   # [osx]

about:
  home: https://github.com/SteemData/steemdata/
  license: MIT
  license_file: '{{ environ["RECIPE_DIR"] }}/LICENSE.txt'
  dev_url: https://github.com/SteemData/steemdata
  doc_url: https://github.com/SteemData/steemdata
  summary: 'Python Utilities for parsing STEEM blockchain'
  description: |
    The goal of the SteemData project is to make data from the 
    STEEM blockchain more accessible to developers, researchers
    and 3rd party services.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - holgern
